transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra at Score Blue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Well...

Speaker 1: Like you can look up my account so that I can—

Speaker 2: The automatic—

Speaker 1: Can do no for a product please.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, can I get your full name and date of birth, sir?

Speaker 1: Sure, it's under Lawrence Blake BLA TV.

Speaker 2: Mr. Blake, I see your prescription here was about five months ago for the hundred milligram Viagra. Is that accurate?

Speaker 1: Yeah, but you just sent me something, I think, 'cause I got charged.

Speaker 2: Look here.

Speaker 1: Mr. Blake, do you have two active accounts with us? I think you might.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so I see one account is through Score Blue and the other is through our partner Ducky MD.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay, so here's what's happening: you have duplicate accounts and it actually is—

Speaker 2: With this would never typically be approved on a normal prescription.

Speaker 1: Because one is for a prescription of Viagra, and then the other is for a prescription of Cialis.

Speaker 2: It is unsafe to combine the two.

Speaker 1: Okay, I need to close out one of these.

Speaker 2: Well, I look, I've got plenty of products, don't need any more, and so did you send me another?

Speaker 1: List of that or just so I see a prescription of—

Speaker 2: The Cialis, which is $54.95, that was shipped out on the 22nd.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: So do you want me to cancel that one and then—

Speaker 1: Yeah, no, please.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I'm going to stop the Cialis. I'm going to cancel that prescription out altogether, okay?

Speaker 1: Because I—I'm married.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: It took me a moment, and I was like, oh, yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And then what regarding the most—

Speaker 2: The other prescription, what I can do for you is—

Speaker 1: In case you want to have refills of the Viagra, I can just extend this pause out.

Speaker 2: And then, you know, I guess that you can call in and place orders as needed should you need some?

Speaker 1: That would be fine.

Speaker 2: I hope not, Mr. Blake, for your sake.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm so appreciative. You can put a hold on that for me?

Speaker 1: Sure, I took care of that for you, both of those.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Wait, so yeah, next time and any orders you need to do, I closed out the Ducky MD account and now it's just strictly—

Speaker 1: Underscore Blue.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, great. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: Super, thank you very much.

Speaker 2: Yep, thank you, sir.
